hostpanel-nodejs v1.0.0 test scenario

1. Build package with ./build.sh.
2. Upload and install hostpanel-nodejs-1.0.0.zip.
3. Verify the package appears in HostPanel installed packages.
4. Verify /app/nodejs loads.
5. Verify /cpanelapi/nodejs/runtime reports Node 18, 20, 22, and 24.
6. Open Add Application.
7. Confirm target domain dropdown lists eligible main domains and subdomains.
8. Confirm cpanel.* and ftp.* domains are excluded.
9. Select a domain and verify application root auto-fills from its document root.
10. Select Node version 22.
11. Select a free port in 31000-31999.
12. Upload or prepare production app files and dependencies under the selected app root.
13. Provision an app with entrypoint server.js.
14. Verify the app DB row exists in nodejs_apps.
15. Verify env vars are stored in nodejs_app_env.
16. Verify systemd service hostpanel-nodejs-<app_id>.service exists.
17. Verify the app starts and reports running.
18. Verify nginx vhost points to 127.0.0.1:<port> on port 80.
19. With SSL already provisioned, verify nginx vhost includes port 443 and existing certificate paths.
20. Open Logs and verify journald output is visible.
21. Edit runtime, port, env, and domain.
22. Verify systemd and nginx configs are regenerated.
23. Delete the app.
24. Verify service and Node-owned nginx config are removed.
25. Verify application files are preserved.
26. Verify audit log entries exist for create, update, start, stop, restart, nginx write, and delete.
